com.ti.debug.engine.scripting

Class ArmAdvancedFeatures

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ti.debug.engine.scripting.ArmAdvancedFeatures

  • public class ArmAdvancedFeatures
extends java.lang.Object
    This class encapsulates the ARM Debug Properties methods. An instance of this class is automatically created when a new session is opened.

    // Create Environment and open a debug session
    ScriptingEnvironment env = new ScriptingEnvironment();
    DebugServer myServer = (DebugServer) env.getServer("DebugServer.1");
    DebugSession mySession = myServer.openSession("*", "*");

    ...

    // Perform flush action
    mySession.armAdvancedFeatures.flushAllCaches();

    ...

    // Get value of property
    bool value = mySession.armAdvancedFeatures.options.getBoolean(id);

    ...

    // set value of property
    mySession.armAdvancedFeatures.options.setBoolean(id,value);

    ...

    // get list of properties, based on regular expression
    mySession.armAdvancedFeatures.options.printOptions(regex);
